rial; font-size:12pt">to support for housing costs. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It seeks </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to address the individual lines of enquiry </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Committee </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">particularly interested. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 11.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Key Reforms to Support for Housing Costs</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are currently 5.1 million people in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Great Britain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in receipt of housing be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nefit. The housing benefit bill increased significantly over the past decade, by around 50 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">per cent in real terms. In 2012/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">13, estimated expenditure was £24 billion.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> If unreformed, expenditure on h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">en</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> over £26 billion by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2014/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">15.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As part of its fiscal consolidation programme, the Government has introduced a number of changes to housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which save over £2 billion by 2014/15</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e first sections of this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">written evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> update</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> on:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reforms to the Local Housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Allowance;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Removal of the spare room subsidy;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Increas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the level of non-dependant deductions;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Introduction of a benefit cap.</span></li></ul></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">next </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">section covers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the replacement of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ouncil </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ax </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit by council tax reduction schemes, designed and administered loca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lly.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">here is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">then </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an update on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">structural changes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">replace </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with the housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">element of Universal Credit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and a reformed scheme </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for pensioners.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This includes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the plans to protect vulnerable groups through</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> managed payment of ren</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to landlords, and special arrangements for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> claimants </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in supported and temporary accommodation.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Finally, there is a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> section on support for home owners. This gives a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n update on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">upport for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ortgage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nterest</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sets out </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the treatment of home owners in Universal Credit and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the reformed scheme for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">pensioners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 11.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Reforms to the Local Housing Allowance</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reforms to Local Housing Allowance (LHA) introduced from April 2011 included setting the rates at the 30th percentile </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rather th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an the median </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of market rents, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capping the maximum LHA rates</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">removing the 5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-bed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and no longer allowing claimants to retain any excess of up to £15 a week between the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ir actual rent and the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> LHA rate.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  From January 2012, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">upper </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">age </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">limit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for the LHA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shared accommodation rate for single people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">without dependent children </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">was </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">raised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">from 25 to 35.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For all these reforms, claimants had up to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nine </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">months</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> transitional protection from their anniversary date, so only started to be affected </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">between January 2012 and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">December</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">providing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£40 million in Discretionary Housing Payments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in 2013/14</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">help</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">make the transition to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">LHA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reforms.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department has commissioned an independent evaluation of the reforms, b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">y a consortium led by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Sheffield</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Hallam</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">University</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nterim </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> was </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">published in May 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-align:justify"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/monitoring-the-impact-of-changes-to-the-local-housing-allowance-system-of-housing-benefit-interim-report-rr-838"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/monitoring-the-impact-of-changes-to-the-local-housing-allowance-system-of-housing-benefit-interim-report-rr-838</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In April 2013, following the announcement made in the June 2010 Budget, increases </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> LHA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">were limited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">using </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Consumer Prices Index (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CPI</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">September 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Rates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">been increased </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">either </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CPI</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">inflation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the 30th percentile of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">market </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, whichever is the lower</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Chancellor announced in his </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Autumn Statement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increases in LHA rates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">would be limited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to 1 per cent in 2014/15 and 2015/16</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. As a result, most LHA rates will be increased in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">April 2014 and April 2015</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">either </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by 1 per cent or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 30th percentile of market rents, whichever is the lower</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Chancello</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">announced that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 30 per cent of the forecast savings </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">from this measure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">would be used </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as Targeted Affordability Funding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to increase the LHA rates in some areas by more than 1 per cent, where rent increases are causing a shortage of affordable accommoda</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department intends to announce </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">autumn </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">how the funding will be targeted</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. This will take account of responses to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that took place </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in July.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Removal of the Spare Room Subsidy</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">April 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the removal of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">spare room subsidy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">means that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">working-age tenants in the social sector receive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit for the number of bedrooms their household needs, bringing the rules in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> line with the private sector.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In December 2011, the Department announced </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the provision </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of £30 million per annum in Discretionary Housing Payments for 2013/14 and 2014/15 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to help people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">make the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">transition to the change</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Of this, £</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">25</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">illion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">per annum </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is specifically to help those living in significantly adapted accommodation who </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are affected</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by the measure.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In July 2013, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">announced </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">further</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in-year funding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of £35 million, again </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to help claimants </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with the transition to the change</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. This comprised:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£10 million transitional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">flexible funding, which the Department has distributed to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">all local authorities using the D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">iscretionary </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ayment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> formula for the removal of the spare room subsidy, which is based </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on working age social sector caseload</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, rent levels and regio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nal levels of under-occupation;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£5 million </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Discretionary Housing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Payments </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for rural areas, which the Department has provided to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the 21 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">least densely populated areas in the country.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">developed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">guidance for local authorities to help </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is directed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to claimants livin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g in isolated rural c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ommunities;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£20 million </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of additional Discretionary Housing Payments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will be available for councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> via a bidding process, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">if they can demonstrate that they are managing their discretionary housing payment allocation in a robust, fair and appropriat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e manner.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department will publish details of the bidding process by October 2013.</span></li></ul></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n total</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the Department is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">providing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£180 million </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of Discretionary Housing Payment funding in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2013/14</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to cover all the welfare reforms, including ‘core’ funding of £20 m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">illion p.a.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department has commissioned </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n independent evaluation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">across </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Great Britain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The consortium </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is led by Ipsos </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">MORI and includes the Cambridge Centre for Housing and Planning Research and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Institute for Fiscal Studies.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Initial findings will be available in 2014 and the final report is due in 2015.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Increasing the Level of Non-Dependant Deductions</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Non-dependants are people who live in a benefit claimant’s household who are not dependant children, for instance adult children, other relatives and friends. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is a long-established principle </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of the benefit system </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">should be expected to contribu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">te towards the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">claimant’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">housing costs. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In the June 2010 Budget, the Chancellor announced a three-year staged increase in the rates o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f non-dependant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">deductions in housing b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">from April 2011. By April 2013, these increases brought the deduction rates</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to the level they would have been had they been increased each year since 2001 to broadly reflect growth in rents. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit non-dependant deduction scheme is based on the age and circumstances of the non-dependant, and deductions are based on standard income-bands. The gross income of the non-dependant determines into which income band the non-dependant falls, and theref</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ore the deduction that should be applied. There are a range of exemptions whereby a deduction does not apply. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department estimates</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that around 350,000 non-dependants are living in households where deductions are made. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction of a Benefit Cap</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he Government believes there has to be a limit to the amount of benefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">entitlement for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">people who are not in work. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Phased implementation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of a cap on benefits </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">started on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">15 April 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in Croydon, Bromley, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Enfield</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and Haringey. National rollout in other lo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cal authorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">began in July and August</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, with the expectation that all appropriate households will be capped by the end of September 2013. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Applying the cap through housing benefit is an interim measure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In the longer term the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department will administer t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cap as part of the Universal Credit system.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Latest figures show around 40,000 households are likely to be affected.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The most vulnerable, including war widows, those in the support group for Employment Support Allowance, and those with severe disabilitie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s are exempt, as are households claiming Working Tax Credit.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Those in supported exempt accommodation will have their housing costs disregarded from the cap calculation. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">here is a 39 week grace period for those who have been in work for 50 of the previous</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 52 weeks immediately preceding their last day of work.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is working with local authorities to provide a wide range of labour market, housing and budgetary related support to help people adjust to the changes. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It has contacted t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hose likely to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be affected well in advance of any change taking place so that they can access this support in good time. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is providing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£65 million in Discretionary Housing Payments </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in 2013/14 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to help those affected by the benefit cap.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n evaluation of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> benefit cap</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">operating under housing benefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will be published in autumn 2014</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Localised Council Tax Reduction Schemes</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Council Tax Benefit was abolished in April 2013 and replaced with council tax reduction schemes, designed and administered locally. Loca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lisation means that authorities make decisions as to how they raise revenue through council tax, and gives them a bigger stake in delivering economic growth.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Council Tax reduction schemes will not form part of Universal Credit, and the award of a reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will have no impact on a claimant's Universal Credit entitlement. However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recognise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that there are important interactions including impacts on work incentives.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">worked with the Department for Communities and Local Govern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(DCLG) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to ensure that local schemes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can support improved work incentives. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">set out the key features of Universal Credit and how local authorities can apply a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sensible means test to U</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">niversal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">redit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> claimants in guidance and in the def</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ault scheme. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and DCLG are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also working to deliver data sharing so that claimants do not have to provide the same information to local authorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">they have already provided to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for their U</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">niversal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">redit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> claim.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Element of Universal Credit</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">8.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For social sector renters, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">element of Universal Credit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">comprises</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rent and eligible service charges</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, less </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">impact from the removal of the spare room subsidy, less any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">housing cost contributions from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">non-dependants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. For private sector renters, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">element </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lower of actual rent and service charges or the appropriate L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ocal Housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">llowance, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">less </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">housing cost contributions from non dependants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">8.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Universal Credit contains a significa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nt change of approach to the treatment of a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">contribution</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to their housing costs by non-dependants.  Instead of the current complex scale of deductions that rise with the non-dependant’s income there is a single</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">flat rate of housing cost contribution which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will apply, irrespective of income, to non-dependants aged 21 and over, where the person is either in work or there is an expectation that they should be working</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can return to work.   A contribution will not be expected if the person is a carer, is resp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onsible for a young child, or is in receipt of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">certain </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">disability benefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 11.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Direct Payments in Universal Credit </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Universal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Credit will help claimants prepare for work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. The Department has designed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the payment arrangements to reflect those that apply to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">working people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Supporting people to manage their finances including paying their rent will ease the transition into paid work.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are advantages in paying the housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">element of Universal Credit direct </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">claimants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, rather than </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as managed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">payme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nts to landlords</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the approac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h currently operating for most housing b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit claimants in the social rented sector. Direct payments </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">encourage people to manage their own budget in the same way as other households. However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also recognise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">importance of stable rental income for social landlords</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which supports them to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">deliver</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new homes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. It has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">develop</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Universal Credit in a way that protects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">landlords’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> financial position.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In summer 2012, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he Department established </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">six direct payment demonst</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ration projects to test how monthly payments of support for housing costs paid directly to most claimants will work in Universal Credit. They will run until the end of 2013.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vidence from the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">projects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">indicates that most people will be able to cope with ma</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">naging a monthly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> budget and paying their rent. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recognises that this is a significant change and that some people will need support, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">including budget management. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">proportion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of claimants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; fo