le="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for management fees of £45 a week</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 11.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Housing and Pensioners</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">12.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For the time being, h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit claimants </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">who have reached the qualifying age for Pension C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">redit will continue to receive housing b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enefit, and those who receive the Guarantee element of Pension</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Credit will continue to receive maximum support with their rent, subject to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any deductions for non</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-dep</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">endants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">12.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Welfare Reform Act 2012 allows for the introduction of a new element of Pension Credit, the Housing Credit, to provide support for rent. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Support for Home Owners </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Chancellor announced in his </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Autumn Statement of 2012 that the support for mortgage interest (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">SMI</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) temporary measures of a shorter 13 week waiting period and a higher £200,000 capital limit for working age claimants will be exte</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nded until the end of March 2015.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Universal Credit retain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the principle of protecting home owners from repossession as far as practicable. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">element for owners is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a standard</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rate of interest on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> outstanding loan up to a set capital limi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a qualifying period before </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">claimants </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are entitled to help.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">some changes in Universal Credit from the scheme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for legacy benefits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Aria