s. </span></li></ul></ul></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department will continue to make managed payments of s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">upport for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tgage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nterest</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to the lender </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">if </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the lender is part of the M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ortgage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nterest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">irect (MID)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> scheme.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">envisages </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the reformed scheme for meeting the housing costs of pensioners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will treat home owners in a broadly similar way to Universal Cred</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.35pt; text-indent:-34pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In the longer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">term, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">intends to move to a system of loans rather than non-recoverable benefits for supporting the housing costs of home owners.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">20 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>